Node.Notes: NpNp assumes: the ravines, [namely th ravines of] Arnon. Possibly NpAdvp: the ravines [in/at] Arnon.
Apparently: from the desert [they went/moved] to Mattanah.
Uncertain. PP-ADV and ClCl assumes: [they went] from Bamoth to the valley that is in the filed of Moab, [and then they went] to the top of Pisgah.
Uncertain. Many think towns/buildings more likely consumed than the masters of Bamoth on the Arnon. See Anchor Bible and WBC commentaries.
With hiphil verb, apparently he did not leave to him a survivor. Most translations seem to change to niphal verb: no survivor was left to him.
